FCS_RBG_EXT.1.1.choice: The application implement DRBG functionality for its cryptographic operations.

FCS_STO_EXT.1.1.choice: The application does not store any credentials to non-volatile memory.

FCS_CKM_EXT.1.1.choice: The application implement asymmetric key generation.

FDP_DEC_EXT.1.1.choice: The application has access to ['camera', 'network connectivity'].

FDP_DEC_EXT.1.2.choice: The application has access to no sensitive information repositories.

FDP_NET_EXT.1.1.choice: The application has user/application initiated network communications.

FDP_DAR_EXT.1.1.choice: The application implement functionality to encrypt sensitive data in non-volatile memory.

FMT_MEC_EXT.1.1.choice: The application invoke the mechanisms recommended by the platform vendor for storing and setting configuration options.

FTP_DIT_EXT.1.1.choice: The application does encrypt some transmitted data with HTTPS/TLS/SSH between itself and another trusted IT product.

FCS_RBG_EXT.2.1,FCS_RBG_EXT.2.2.choice: The application perform all deterministic random bit generation (DRBG) services in accordance with NIST Special Publication 800-90A using Hash_DRBG. The deterministic RBG is seeded by an entropy source that accumulates entropy from a platform-based DRBG and a software-based noise source, with a minimum of 256 bits of entropy at least equal to the greatest security strength (according to NIST SP 800-57) of the keys and hashes that it will generate.

FCS_CKM.1.1(1).choice: The application generate asymmetric cryptographic keys not in accordance with FCS_CKM.1.1(1) using key generation algorithm RSA schemes and cryptographic key sizes of 1024-bit or lower.

FCS_CKM.1.1(3),FCS_CKM.1.2(3).choice: A password/passphrase shall perform [Password-based Key Derivation Functions] in accordance with a specified cryptographic algorithm..

FCS_COP.1.1(1).choice: The application perform encryption/decryption not in accordance with FCS_COP.1.1(1), AES-ECB mode is being used.

FCS_HTTPS_EXT.1.2.choice: The application implement HTTPS using TLS.

FCS_HTTPS_EXT.1.3.choice: The application notify the user and not establish the connection or request application authorization to establish the connection if the peer certificate is deemed invalid.

FIA_X509_EXT.1.1.choice: The application invoked platform-provided functionality to validate certificates in accordance with the following rules: ['The application validate a certificate path by ensuring the presence of the basicConstraints extension and that the CA flag is set to TRUE for all CA certificates'].

FIA_X509_EXT.1.2.choice: The application treat a certificate as a CA certificate only if the basicConstraints extension is present and the CA flag is set to TRUE.

FIA_X509_EXT.2.1.choice: The application use X.509v3 certificates as defined by RFC 5280 to support authentication for HTTPS , TLS.

FIA_X509_EXT.2.2.choice: When the application cannot establish a connection to determine the validity of a certificate, the application allow the administrator to choose whether to accept the certificate in these cases or accept the certificate ,or not accept the certificate.

FCS_CKM.1.1(2).choice: The application shall generate symmetric cryptographic keys using a Random Bit Generator as specified in FCS_RBG_EXT.1 and specified cryptographic key sizes 128 bit or 256 bit.

"info_text" : "This is a native Android Ethereum light client wallet.

It uses the in process node as ethereum light client from the go-ethereum project.

Big shout out to karalabe, fjl, zsfelfoldi and obscuren here - awesome work!

This alpha uses the testnet.

Bitlumens is trying to be as decentralized as possible. Hence it is using a light client and not centralized pre-configured nodes. Unfortunately we cannot be fully decentralized yet. For getting the exchange rates for (fiat) references we are querying cryptocompare and to get transactions we use the great etherscan.io service. The app will work if these services are down for some reason - but you might miss some features like up to date exchange rates. As soon as it is possible to get these things in a decentralized manner we will try to use it.

Our wonderful Icon is from Michael Cook.

Be aware that this is an alpha and there will be bugs. There are also some known issues like this one and this one

The project was started by ligi as this is not only needed as a wallet - but also as a building block for the espass project

The project is libre software (aka FOSS/free/open source) - you can find code and open issues on the Bitlumens GitHub Organisation

Please have a great time with this app and we are happy about feedback, donations, pull-requests ..-)

The ideal place for feedback is our sub-reddit https://www.reddit.com/r/walleth You can find the source on github"

"info_text" : "これはネイティブの Android Ethereum 軽量クライアントウォレットです。

go-ethereum プロジェクトから、Ethereum 軽量クライアントとしてインプロセスノードを使用します。

karalabe, fjl, zsfelfoldi および obscuren の素晴らしい仕事に大変感謝します!

このアルファはtestnet を使用します。

Bitlumens は可能な限り分散化しようとしています。 したがって、集中型の事前構成済みのノードではなく、軽いクライアントを使用しています。 残念ながら、まだ完全に分散化することはできません。 (フィアット) 参照の為替レートを取得するために、cryptocompare に照会し、素晴らしい etherscan.io サービスを使用してトランダクションを取得します。 何かの理由でこれらのサービスがダウンしてもアプリは動作しますが、為替レートの更新などの一部の機能は使えません。 これらのものが分散化されて入手できるようになると、すぐにそれを使用しようとします。

素晴らしいアイコンは Michael Cook の作成です。

これはアルファ版であり、バグがあるかもしれないことにご注意ください。 これ または これ ような既知のバグがあるかもしれません。

プロジェクトは ligi によって、ウォレットとしてのみの必要性からだけでなく espass プロジェクトのビルディングブロックとして始まりました

プロジェクトは無料のソフトウェアです (別名 FOSS/フリー/オープンソース) - Bitlumens GitHub 組織 でコードを見たり、問題を報告することができます

このアプリですばらしい時間をお過ごしください。フィードバック、寄付、プルリクエストをお待ちしています ..-)

フィードバックの理想的な場所は、sub-reddit https://www.reddit.com/r/walleth です ソースは github で見つけることができます"

"request_hint_test_net" : "ソーシャルメディアでこのアドレスをハッシュタグ #walleth で共有して、テスト Ether を入手することができます。
LIGI は Twitter をモニターして、のローンチしたテスト Ether を集めました。
あなたも手に入れたテスト Ether を、このハッシュタグを使用して見つけたユーザーに渡して、この方法でトランザクションを練習することができます。"

"settings_start_light_summary" : "This makes your phone warm, might crash and use a lot of CPU cycles and bandwidth - but also gives you the warm feeling of helping decentralisation by finding issues in this area."

"info_text" : "This is a native Android Ethereum wallet.

Bitlumens is trying to be as decentralized as possible. Hence it is offering a light. But light clients are still in early development. We cannot be fully decentralized *yet*. For getting the exchange rates for (fiat) references we are querying cryptocompare and to get transactions we use the great etherscan.io service. The app should work if these services are down for some reason - but you might miss some features like up to date exchange rates. As soon as it is possible to get these things in a decentralized manner we will try to use it.

Our wonderful Icon is from Michael Cook.

The base for the send and receive icons are made by Catalin Fertu from flaticon.com

The light client comes via the go-ethereum project. Big shout out to karalabe, holiman, fjl, zsfelfoldi and obscuren here - awesome work!

Be aware that this is an alpha and there will be bugs.

The project was started by ligi as this is not only needed as a wallet - but also as a building block for the espass project

The project is libre software (aka FOSS/free/open source) - you can find code and open issues on the Bitlumens GitHub Organisation

Find the opensource licenses here.

Please have a great time with this app and we are happy about feedback, donations, pull-requests ..-)

The ideal place for feedback is our sub-reddit https://www.reddit.com/r/walleth You can find the source on github and more information on the Blog."

playstore_details.title: BitLumens Ethereum Wallet
playstore_details.description:
Highlights of BitLumens - Ethereum wallet

 Participate in any ERC20 or ERC223 based ICO or airdrop. Configure gas price, gas limit and data/message in a simple and easy-to-understand way

 Take the full advantage of Ethereum platform. Send, receive, store and track Ethereum (ETH) Token.

 Maintain control of your digital assets by storing your private keys on your own device. With Trust Wallet’s server-free infrastructure only you can access your funds

 Protect your crypto funds by enabling additional level of security -TREZOR Support (via USB-OTG - model 1 and model T).
 
 JSON UTC key import/export
